Figure 4a is the UV-vis diffuse reflectance spectrum (DRS) of Bi2WO6, Ag2S and Bi2WO6/Ag2S heterostructures. Flower-like Bi2WO6 exhibits photo-absorption from UV light to visible light, and the absorption edge locates at ~450 nm. After surface modification with Ag2S, an obvious red shift in the absorption edge can be observed. The absorption edge of the Bi2WO6/Ag2S extends to ~550 nm because of the coupling of Ag2S nanoparticles with Bi2WO6 nanoplates. The optical bandgaps of a semiconductor can be calculated using the following equation [39]:Fig. 4
a UV-vis absorption spectra of Bi2WO6, Ag2S and Bi2WO6/Ag2S. b Kubelka-Munk plot for bandgap calculation of Bi2WO6, Ag2S, and Bi2WO6/Ag2S(αhv)1n=A(hv−Eg)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
